subSubSection.paragraph:
Many species, especially of the 

Dim. gracilis

group, have restricted mountainous distributions, whereas others are more widely distributed in littoral meadows and on the grassy steppes of North Africa (
Wagner & Weber, 1964
; 
Ehanno & Ribes, 1994
). It is thought the restricted ranges of many species may be the result of the high degree of brachyptery expressed in the genus, particularly in females (
Linnavuori, 1992
).
